Mbungo is also a Fifa international physical trainer and is the only Rwandan coach to have won a silverware without coaching Rayon Sports and APR FC.He coached AFC Leopards in 2019 before parting ways with them in  December 2019  over unpaid dues. Bandari Football Club Monday unveiled former AFC Leopards coach Andre Cassa Mbungo as their new head coach, filling the void that was left by Ken Odhiambo, who decamped to Sofapaka a fortnight ago.
The 52-year-old Rwandan national becomes Bandari’s third tactician in less than a year and 11th since the team regained promotion to top flight football in 2008. He has signed a two year contract  with the Dockers.



