Andre Cassa Mbungo holds a CAF A coaching badge and played for Dynamo and Athletic of Burundi between 1984 and 1994, before returning to Rwanda to begin his coaching career.
Mbungo says he horned his skills by starting to handle lower division clubs from 2002 before taking over at Kiyovu SC in 2006 and later Police FC in 2007 and SEC Academy in 2011.
He also won the Rwanda Cup (Peace Cup) with AS Kigali in 2013, before taking the Citizens Football Club to the third round of the Caf Confederation Cup for the first time the following year.
Mbungo is also a Fifa international physical trainer and is the only Rwandan coach to have won a silverware without coaching Rayon Sports and APR FC.
He coached AFC Leopards in 2019 before parting ways with them in December 2019 over unpaid dues. FC Tokyo pocketed Sh79.2 million alongside lifting the trophy. Kajiado All Stars opened the scoring sheet in the round of 16 clash after just four seconds. Pope Francis has accepted his resignation, which came after he attained the mandatory retirement age. Nyeri Town MP Mr Ngunjiri Wambugu said Mr Kang’ata was not sincere in his letter for sharing it with the media and the public. Learning institutions were shut in March to contain the spread of the coronavirus.